# Tests and fixtures

- Find the Makefile target that owns a test file with
  `./bin/wtest changed <file>` and run exactly that target; fall back to
  `make tests` only when the mapping says so.
- `*fixture*.w` files are compile-only inputs whose exact diagnostics are
  asserted by grep in the Makefile (`warning_test`,
  `type_system_error_test`, `check_json_test`, ...). Editing one usually
  requires updating the asserted message text or line numbers in the same
  commit. The automatic edit-check hook deliberately skips fixture paths.
- A new end-to-end test needs: the `tests/foo_test.w` program (use
  `lib/assert.w` / `lib/testing.w` helpers), a Makefile target, the same
  target in `build.json`, membership in the `tests` umbrella in both, and
  a mapping entry in `tools/test_map.w` when a directory rule does not
  already cover it.
- Test programs may use any syntax the current compiler supports (they
  are compiled with `bin/wv2`, not the seed).
